  <discussion>Anulocaulis leiosolenus occurs as isolated, islandlike populations that are
    homogeneous within but differ slightly between populations. The turbinate fruits with prominent
    ribs and equatorial flange ridge, and the long-tubular perianths, are unifying features.
    Pubescence, when present, is inconspicuous on the perianth, and is best seen on tips of mature
    buds.</discussion>
